1
00:00:11,267 --> 00:00:15,000
<i>I want to see Emma so I can show
her how much I hate her.</i>

2
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:18,467
<i>And to tell her not to show up
to our daughter ever again.</i>

3
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:20,033
<i> The fight is over, Emma.</i>

4
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:22,233
<i> I've just won the war.</i>

5
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:23,433
<i> I like you, Mooks.</i>

6
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:27,100
<i>I like you that it hurts
seeing you hurting.</i>

7
00:00:27,233 --> 00:00:28,200
<i> You like me?</i>

8
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:30,033
<i>I won't push myself on you
anymore, Mooks.</i>

9
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:31,567
<i> Even as friends.</i>

10
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:35,333
<i>Think about why
you're doing this</i>

11
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:36,600
<i> and who you're doing it for.</i>

12
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:38,867
<i> I'm ready for you, Jade.</i>

13
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,833
<i> I'll haunt you.</i>

14
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:44,533
<i>I'll drive you crazy
like you did to me.</i>

15
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:48,900
<i>Pour all your love
into our family. Okay?</i>

16
00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:52,833
<i>I think a noise came from there.</i>

17
00:00:52,967 --> 00:00:54,933
<i>What's that?
Did you hear it, Jade?</i>

18
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,067
Love, stop.

19
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:48,800
Are you already drunk?
That's enough.

20
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:51,633
What drunk are you talking
about?

21
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:53,067
I just had four bottles.

22
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,067
I won't get drunk even if
I consume ten bottles of this.

23
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:58,533
- I really heard something.
- Well..

24
00:01:58,667 --> 00:02:00,233
It seems like someone's
knocking. I heard a thud.

25
00:02:00,367 --> 00:02:02,433
Love, I don't hear anything.

26
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:04,500
Nothing.

27
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:06,367
There's nothing.
There's no sound.

28
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:08,867
I don't know
what you're talking about.

29
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,933
- Jade, no. Listen.
- Love.

30
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:14,367
Okay, fine. I will.

31
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:27,233
Ouch.

32
00:02:33,467 --> 00:02:35,433
Sorry, sorry.

33
00:02:35,567 --> 00:02:37,267
I didn't mean to do that.

34
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,833
It's just that it's what I do
when I get hurt.

35
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:42,667
It's okay. I did that, too,
when I was young.

36
00:02:46,367 --> 00:02:50,067
Anyway, I need to go
to the bar later.

37
00:02:51,367 --> 00:02:53,400
We have a meeting.

38
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:54,500
Aren't you running late already?

39
00:02:56,767 --> 00:02:57,933
No.

40
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:02,133
Emma...

41
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:04,500
I want to say sorry.

42
00:03:04,633 --> 00:03:09,500
Maybe I shouldn't have let you
hold a gun right away.

43
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:11,867
Maybe I should first teach you
all the basic things

44
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,733
you should know.

45
00:03:13,867 --> 00:03:17,867
So, we'll focus on that
when we return.

46
00:03:19,267 --> 00:03:19,900
Okay.

47
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:22,300
But I'll start haunting Jade.

48
00:03:24,733 --> 00:03:27,133
Aren't you rushing it?

49
00:03:27,267 --> 00:03:30,200
Logan, I need to do that before
Mookie's life gets ruined

50
00:03:30,333 --> 00:03:32,467
because of what Jade's
been teaching her.

51
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,433
Okay.

52
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:28,333
<i> Danilo, Mookie...</i>

53
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:31,300
<i> I'm here in the basement.</i>

54
00:04:31,433 --> 00:04:33,767
<i> Olive locked me up here.</i>

55
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:37,633
<i> She's not Jade. She's Olive.</i>

56
00:04:39,167 --> 00:04:42,833
See? Nothing. No sound.

57
00:04:42,967 --> 00:04:44,800
Earlier...

58
00:04:46,033 --> 00:04:48,267
Are you okay?

59
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,600
Maybe you're right.

60
00:04:49,733 --> 00:04:52,167
I'm already drunk.

61
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:58,000
I heard something earlier.
But, okay.

62
00:04:58,133 --> 00:05:00,000
I'll just make some coffee,
okay?

63
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,467
Okay. I'll wait for you here.

64
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,633
Ligaya?

65
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:24,800
Where?

66
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:28,100
What the heck!
Let go of me! Stop!

67
00:06:31,533 --> 00:06:35,300
What are you doing?
Let go of me!

68
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:43,667
What the heck!

69
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:47,200
<i>What's this?
Take this off of me!</i>

70
00:06:47,533 --> 00:06:48,800
Ligaya!

71
00:06:51,933 --> 00:06:53,100
<i>Where do you think you're going?</i>

72
00:06:58,267 --> 00:06:59,400
Ligaya!

73
00:07:04,767 --> 00:07:08,233
Where do you think you're going?
You can't leave yet!

74
00:07:08,367 --> 00:07:12,000
Because you still owe me a lot!

75
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:13,033
Come here!

76
00:07:16,067 --> 00:07:19,300
I won't let you ruin my life
again.

77
00:07:19,433 --> 00:07:20,667
Not now.

78
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,400
Not ever!

79
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:54,367
Come here.

80
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,067
You can't go anywhere.

81
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:09,733
Okay.

82
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:17,800
Logan, I'm the one injured,
but you're the one shaking.

83
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:24,433
This is my first time putting
a bandage on someone else.

84
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,000
I'm sorry.

85
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,300
<i> Your wound is almost healed.</i>

86
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,233
<i> Can you get up?</i>

87
00:08:46,367 --> 00:08:47,633
<i> Yes.</i>

88
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:50,033
<i> Hold on to me.</i>

89
00:08:50,167 --> 00:08:51,100
Are you okay?

90
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,067
I miss Mookie so much.

91
00:08:56,267 --> 00:08:57,867
Her voice,

92
00:08:59,033 --> 00:09:00,900
her embrace...

93
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:08,633
Just a little more time,
and you'll get her back.

94
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:31,500
Logan, look.

95
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:34,233
It seems that Mookie's going
through something.

96
00:09:34,367 --> 00:09:35,767
I need to see her.

97
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:38,133
Emma, don't.

98
00:09:38,267 --> 00:09:39,600
You might get caught.

99
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:42,300
But my daughter needs me.

100
00:09:42,433 --> 00:09:44,567
Her father's there.

101
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:50,267
Emma, let Danilo help her
handle her problem.

102
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:53,333
We don't want to ruin our plans
just because of that.

103
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:59,300
That's why I'm doing this.
For Mookie. I'm a mother.

104
00:09:59,433 --> 00:10:03,100
I can't be at peace until I see
what's happening to her.

105
00:10:03,267 --> 00:10:04,633
I'll just check on her.

106
00:10:04,767 --> 00:10:06,700
I want to know
if she's doing okay.

107
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:13,667
Fine. Okay.

108
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:18,667
But I can't miss my important
meeting later.

109
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,733
I can't go with you.

110
00:10:20,867 --> 00:10:23,000
I'll be okay.
I can manage on my own.

111
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:29,067
No, I'll tell Marco
to go with you.

112
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:32,533
But, Emma, be careful.

113
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:35,300
I'll go home to change clothes.

114
00:10:35,467 --> 00:10:37,533
Please tell Marco to pick me up.

115
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:09,567
Dad?

116
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:12,067
Dear.

117
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:15,233
Are you okay?
Have you eaten yet?

118
00:11:15,367 --> 00:11:15,833
Come here.

119
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,500
I'm okay. I'm not hungry.

120
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:24,000
What are you doing here?

121
00:11:24,133 --> 00:11:29,433
I think I heard a noise
downstairs.

122
00:11:29,567 --> 00:11:30,833
Someone's yelling.

123
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:34,400
I want to check it.

124
00:11:34,533 --> 00:11:35,633
Love?

125
00:11:35,767 --> 00:11:36,767
Mookie?

126
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:37,833
Jade.

127
00:11:37,967 --> 00:11:39,933
What are you doing here?

128
00:11:40,067 --> 00:11:41,233
Wait.

129
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:47,233
- Well...
- Love.

130
00:11:49,133 --> 00:11:55,867
I think I heard people yelling.

131
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,367
That's why I came here to check.

132
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,033
Oh, that?

133
00:12:00,167 --> 00:12:01,433
It's me, Love.

134
00:12:02,633 --> 00:12:03,867
You're right.

135
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:06,167
I also heard a noise from here.

136
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:07,633
That's why I came here.

137
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:11,633
And true enough,
I saw the culprit.

138
00:12:11,767 --> 00:12:14,867
There's a big rat inside.

139
00:12:15,033 --> 00:12:18,967
My gosh! I was surprised.
That's why I yelled.

140
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:20,567
Rat?

141
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:21,933
You went to see the rat?

142
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:23,467
Of course, I went to check.

143
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:26,000
I was so annoyed
because it was so noisy.

144
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:30,867
I was surprised to see
a large rat so I yelled.

145
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,933
You should've called me
so I could help you.

146
00:12:34,067 --> 00:12:35,867
Don't worry about it, Love.

147
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,333
Everything's good.

148
00:12:37,467 --> 00:12:41,667
I did the best that I could.
Looks like it's already dead.

149
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:45,700
Anyway, Mookie,
I know you're still upset.

150
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:48,633
Do you want us to eat out?

151
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,267
At your favorite restaurant?

152
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,167
I don't want to go out.

153
00:12:54,533 --> 00:12:56,100
Okay, then.

154
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:58,667
I'll just order
your favorite food.

155
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:04,233
Let's eat on the terrace
so we can catch some fresh air.

156
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,300
We all need that right now.

157
00:13:10,867 --> 00:13:12,500
<i> Oh, yes, we do.</i>

158
00:13:12,633 --> 00:13:18,533
<i>We need to celebrate Emma's
delicious, tragic death.</i>

159
00:13:18,667 --> 00:13:21,367
So, Mookie, change your clothes.

160
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:23,333
Then we'll eat.

161
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:25,433
Let's go. Let's eat.

162
00:13:27,767 --> 00:13:28,567
What's this?

163
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:32,600
Probably some trash.

164
00:13:32,733 --> 00:13:34,200
Just throw it on the way.

165
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:36,033
It looks like a letter.

166
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,500
<i>Where do you think you're going?</i>

167
00:13:47,633 --> 00:13:49,367
<i> You can't leave yet.</i>

168
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:53,067
<i>Because you still owe me a lot!</i>

169
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:55,067
<i> Come here!</i>

170
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:05,733
I think this is mine.

171
00:14:13,233 --> 00:14:13,967
Why?

172
00:14:15,967 --> 00:14:17,200
Nothing.

173
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,500
It has my notes for Artemis
Pharmacy's launch

174
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:22,800
of its newest medicine,
the Activora.

175
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:24,933
There are so many mistakes.

176
00:14:25,067 --> 00:14:27,067
I need to redo it.

177
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,767
Are you sure you're okay?

178
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:31,167
Of course!

179
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:33,167
Nothing I can't handle.

180
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:35,400
Go on, Mookie.
Change your clothes.

181
00:14:35,533 --> 00:14:37,000
Love, go with her.

182
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,733
I'll join you for dinner.

183
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:41,000
Okay. Let's go. Come on, dear.

184
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:15,333
<i> Ligaya, you almost exposed me.</i>

185
00:15:15,467 --> 00:15:18,033
<i>You're no longer
just a nuisance.</i>

186
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,400
<i> You're becoming a threat.</i>

187
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:37,333
Jade ordered a lot of food.

188
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,667
It seems like we're celebrating
something.

189
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:44,133
Here. Have some juice first.

190
00:15:56,367 --> 00:15:57,467
Mookie,

191
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:01,300
I know you were hurt by the
information about your mom

192
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:04,333
that your Aunt Jade told you.

193
00:16:04,467 --> 00:16:06,133
Me, too. I got hurt.

194
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:11,733
Maybe we should just accept it.

195
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:17,800
Dad, let's not talk about her.

196
00:16:21,633 --> 00:16:25,933
I don't want to waste my time
on her anymore.

197
00:16:26,067 --> 00:16:29,000
If she doesn't like us,
then be it.

198
00:16:29,133 --> 00:16:30,933
She can do whatever she wants.

199
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:35,767
But what's your post
on your social media about?

200
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,267
Dear, sorry.

201
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:43,100
I checked your
social media page.

202
00:16:43,267 --> 00:16:47,167
I'm your father.
I'm worried about you.

203
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:51,267
Just ignore it, Dad.
It's not about mom, okay?

204
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:57,033
Besides, I decided not to think
about her anymore.

205
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:59,533
So you're worried about
something?

206
00:17:01,133 --> 00:17:02,600
Tell me about it, dear.

207
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:06,500
I can't promise,
but maybe I can help.

208
00:17:06,633 --> 00:17:08,533
What is it about?

209
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:09,967
Is it about school?

210
00:17:11,233 --> 00:17:12,900
Ma'am, Sir! I'll go home now.

211
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:16,033
- Okay, Loida.
- Be safe!

212
00:17:19,067 --> 00:17:21,900
Dear, what is it about?
Is it about school?

213
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:25,633
<i> You've changed a lot.</i>

214
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:27,500
<i>You're no longer
the Mookie I know.</i>

215
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:30,267
<i>I won't push myself on you
anymore, Mooks.</i>

216
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,767
<i> Even as friends.</i>

217
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:32,967
<i> Bye, Mooks.</i>

218
00:17:35,133 --> 00:17:37,433
Dad, it's not a big deal.

219
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:01,767
It's not a big deal,
but your face says otherwise.

220
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:03,867
You look like the man on
the five hundred peso bill.

221
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:04,967
You look sad.

222
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:07,200
It's not funny.

223
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:10,433
I'm sorry for not being funny.
I'm not a comedian.

224
00:18:10,567 --> 00:18:14,167
But I just want to make you
feel better.

225
00:18:18,033 --> 00:18:20,300
I'm okay, Dad.

226
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:23,000
Don't worry.

227
00:18:23,167 --> 00:18:25,000
Are you sure you're okay now?

228
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,700
Come here.

229
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:33,867
I'm always here whenever
you're not feeling okay.

230
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:40,000
Your dad has a big collection
of corny jokes.

231
00:18:42,067 --> 00:18:42,800
Come here.

232
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:52,667
<i>I want to show up in front
of you.</i>

233
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:55,067
<i> But I'm not ready yet.</i>

234
00:18:55,233 --> 00:18:59,267
<i> You won't believe what I say.</i>

235
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:02,633
<i>I need to prove Jade's
evilness first.</i>

236
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:05,633
<i>So that when we face each other,</i>

237
00:19:05,767 --> 00:19:10,967
<i>I have solid proof
of that woman's wickedness.</i>

238
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:35,767
Thank you, dear. We're now okay.

239
00:19:36,533 --> 00:19:38,000
I missed you.

240
00:19:41,867 --> 00:19:46,400
Sorry, Dad, for giving you
the attitude.

241
00:19:46,967 --> 00:19:49,100
Don't worry about that.

242
00:19:49,233 --> 00:19:52,800
What matters is we're okay now.

243
00:19:52,933 --> 00:20:01,900
I don't want us to fight.
It doesn't feel good.

244
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:04,133
I know, Dad.

245
00:20:06,167 --> 00:20:07,633
Wait.

246
00:20:07,767 --> 00:20:10,200
Where's Auntie Jade?

247
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:15,100
Maybe she's doing something
inside.

248
00:20:16,067 --> 00:20:18,033
Come on.
Let's have some juice first.

249
00:20:18,167 --> 00:20:19,200
Come on.

250
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:21,700
Let's wait for your Auntie Jade.

251
00:20:33,867 --> 00:20:34,833
You know what?

252
00:20:37,433 --> 00:20:40,100
I only have a simple dream.

253
00:20:42,633 --> 00:20:44,633
And that is to have
a complete family.

254
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:48,433
Because...

255
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:52,300
all my life,

256
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:56,267
I haven't experienced that.

257
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,933
And it's all because of you.

258
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:07,400
Because you gave me up to people
who didn't love me.

259
00:21:08,567 --> 00:21:09,867
But look at me now.

260
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:13,267
I survived all that.

261
00:21:14,533 --> 00:21:18,800
And my dream of having
a complete family

262
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:21,100
is about to come true...

263
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:26,667
because of Danilo and Mookie.

264
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:31,233
But here you are...

265
00:21:32,667 --> 00:21:37,100
trying to hinder my happiness.

266
00:21:46,700 --> 00:21:47,567
Why is Jade taking so long?

267
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:50,500
Mookie, come on.
Let's not wait for Jade.

268
00:21:50,633 --> 00:21:54,467
- Let's eat.
- Yeah, Dad. I'm starving.

269
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:56,633
- This looks delicious.
- Emma?

270
00:21:56,767 --> 00:21:58,200
Emma!

271
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:02,500
Emma!

272
00:22:07,967 --> 00:22:10,233
I saw Emma!

273
00:22:10,367 --> 00:22:11,167
Mookie!

274
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:15,867
What? Mom isn't here.

275
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:17,867
No, she was there. Wait.

276
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:18,867
Dad, what's wrong with you?

277
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:19,500
I'll go there.

278
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:20,933
What's wrong with you?

279
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:23,133
Are you drunk?

280
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:27,033
You reek of alcohol,
I just don't say it.

281
00:22:27,167 --> 00:22:29,000
You and your Aunt Jade
are the same.

282
00:22:29,133 --> 00:22:30,500
I'm not drunk.

283
00:22:30,633 --> 00:22:33,833
I saw your mom. Wait.
I'll go to her.

284
00:22:34,867 --> 00:22:35,933
Dad!

285
00:22:36,067 --> 00:22:37,767
Dad, what are you doing? Wait!

286
00:22:39,767 --> 00:22:41,833
How is it?

287
00:22:41,967 --> 00:22:43,200
I saw my husband and daughter.

288
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:44,500
They were happy.

289
00:22:44,633 --> 00:22:46,533
And Jade wasn't there.

290
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:49,933
I'm happy to see
my daughter's smile.

291
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:51,333
Do you feel okay now?

292
00:22:51,467 --> 00:22:52,167
Yes.

293
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:53,467
- Let's go?
- Let's go.

294
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:58,467
Dad!

295
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:00,133
Dad, what are you doing?

296
00:23:05,867 --> 00:23:08,833
You need to consult a doctor.

297
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:12,067
I'll go with you.
I won't leave you.

298
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:14,033
I'll make it up to you, dear.

299
00:23:14,167 --> 00:23:15,800
What do you think of me?

300
00:23:15,933 --> 00:23:17,400
Crazy?

301
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:20,067
I'm not crazy, Ligaya!

302
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,300
You!

303
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:22,900
You're the crazy one!

304
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:24,300
You!

305
00:23:24,433 --> 00:23:25,967
Let's focus on our plan, okay?

306
00:23:26,100 --> 00:23:30,367
You'll drive Jade crazy before
you show up to Mookie.

307
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:32,033
She's so evil.

308
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:37,433
I will never forgive
what she did to me and dad.

309
00:23:37,567 --> 00:23:38,833
It's okay.

310
00:23:38,967 --> 00:23:40,500
I'm here for you.

311
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:45,100
Artemis Pharmacy will launch
the new vitamin of Ramirez Lab.

312
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:46,800
We're going to attend it.

313
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:51,267
That's where I'll haunt Jade
and seduce Danilo.

314
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:54,000
Love?

315
00:23:55,867 --> 00:23:58,100
Why are you looking
at that woman?
